# E2E Testing Patterns

## When to Use Which Tool

| Use Case | Tool |
|---|---|
| CI pipeline, cross-browser matrix, parallel execution, deterministic assertions | Playwright |
| AI agent recon, interactive exploration, Pencil design comparison, visual QA | agent-browser |

Both tools share `data-testid` selectors, `e2e/test-assets/` audio files, and the `?e2e_auto_login=true` auth pattern.

---

## Playwright Patterns

### NEVER Use Timeouts

```typescript
// FORBIDDEN
await page.waitForTimeout(5000);
await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle');

// REQUIRED - wait for conditions
await page.waitForSelector('[data-message-complete="true"]');
await page.waitForURL(/\/c\//);
await expect(element).toBeVisible();
```

### Wait for AI Response Completion

```typescript
await page.waitForSelector('[data-message-role="assistant"][data-message-complete="true"]');
```

### Dismiss Changelog Modal

Always call `dismissChangelogModal(page)` after auth - the modal blocks all interactions.

### Use waitForSelector for Long Operations

`expect().toBeVisible()` has 5s timeout. Use `waitForSelector` (30s) for slow ops:

```typescript
await page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="my-element"]', { timeout: 30000 });
```

### File Uploads (Playwright)

```typescript
// Synthetic file from buffer
await page.setInputFiles('#file-upload', {
  name: 'sample.mp3',
  mimeType: 'audio/mpeg',
  buffer: Buffer.from('fake-audio-binary'),
});

// Real file from test assets
await page.setInputFiles('[data-testid="hidden-file-input"]', 'e2e/test-assets/test-audio.mp3');
```

### API Mocking (Playwright only)

```typescript
await page.route('**/api/upload-audio', async (route) => {
  await route.fulfill({
    status: 200,
    contentType: 'application/json',
    body: JSON.stringify({ content_id: 'e2e-uuid', transcription: 'Hello' }),
  });
});
```

