## agent-browser Patterns

### Core Workflow

```bash
# 1. Navigate
agent-browser open "http://localhost:3000/enhance-transcribe?e2e_auto_login=true"

# 2. Wait for auth, then snapshot interactive elements
sleep 3 && agent-browser snapshot -i

# 3. Interact using refs from snapshot output
agent-browser click @e9              # click by ref
agent-browser fill @e2 "search text" # fill by ref

# 4. Semantic element targeting (accessible name)
agent-browser find role button click --name "Start Transcription"
agent-browser find role link click --name "New Chat"
agent-browser find role tab click --name "Summary"

# 5. Screenshot for visual comparison
agent-browser screenshot e2e/agent-browser/artifacts/feature/01-step-name.png

# 6. Re-snapshot after any page state change (refs are ephemeral)
agent-browser snapshot -i
```

### File Uploads (agent-browser)

No JS eval needed. Use the `upload` command with the hidden file input selector:

```bash
agent-browser upload '[data-testid="hidden-file-input"]' e2e/test-assets/test-audio.mp3
```

### Mobile Viewport Emulation

```bash
agent-browser set device "iPhone 12"   # 390x844 with touch
agent-browser set viewport 1024 768    # custom desktop size
```

### JS Evaluation (escape hatch)

```bash
agent-browser eval "document.querySelector('[data-testid=\"my-el\"]')?.innerText || 'not found'"
```

### Chromium Launch Arguments

Pass custom Chromium flags for special capabilities:

```bash
# Via CLI flag
agent-browser --args "--use-fake-device-for-media-stream,--use-fake-ui-for-media-stream"

# Via environment variable
AGENT_BROWSER_ARGS="--use-fake-device-for-media-stream" agent-browser open http://localhost:3000
```

### Test-User Helpers (`window.__e2e`)

Available when `?e2e_auto_login=true` is active. Use via `agent-browser eval`:

```bash
agent-browser eval "window.__e2e.openSidebar()"
agent-browser eval "window.__e2e.has('transcription-result-screen')"
agent-browser eval "window.__e2e.clickButton('Start Transcription')"
agent-browser eval "window.__e2e.clickFirstMemory()"
```

URL params for auto-setup: `&e2e_sidebar=open`, `&e2e_goto=first-memory`

Shell helpers: `source src/e2e/agent-browser-helpers.sh` for `e2e_has`, `e2e_click`, `e2e_poll`, `check` (with auto-screenshot on failure).

Full API reference: see `.cursor/rules/agent-browser-defaults.mdc`

### Key Behaviors

- Chromium auto-grants mic/camera permissions (no dialog), but `MediaRecorder` produces no audio data without `--use-fake-device-for-media-stream`
- Native dialogs: `confirm()` returns true by default, `prompt()` returns default value
- Refs (`@e1`, `@e2`) are ephemeral -- re-snapshot after any navigation or state change
- Auth via `?e2e_auto_login=true` works identically to Playwright

### Screenshot Artifacts Convention

```
e2e/agent-browser/artifacts/{feature}/
  01-idle-desktop.png
  02-setup-fast-model.png
  03-in-progress.png
  04-result-transcript.png
  05-mobile-idle.png
```

### Pencil Design Comparison

Compare agent-browser screenshots against Pencil MCP design references:

```bash
# 1. Get design reference (via Pencil MCP get_screenshot tool)
# 2. Get live screenshot
agent-browser screenshot e2e/agent-browser/artifacts/enhance-transcribe/01-idle-desktop.png
# 3. Compare structure, layout, element presence (not text content)
```

